Description: Poyzd brings individuals and organizations together on an internet scale to solve complex, multidimensional problems.
Full Description: Poyzd is a tool for bringing individuals and organizations together on an internet scale to solve complex, multidimensional problems. Poyzd is a double bottom line business.  It generates revenues and is an instrument of collective impact. Web 2.0 tools are adequate for raising issues and addressing single-dimensional issues.  Their use in tackling more difficult problems is frustrates users with a absence of closure. Facilitated, face-to-face dialogue methods may be the most powerful techniques ever developed for characterizing a problem space, but they are expensive, time intensive, require a trained facilitator, and fail to nimbly respond to changes in the situation.  For over 60 years, these shortfalls have prevented widespread adoption of dialogue techniques. Poyzd adapts and extends the core functions of facilitated dialogue for the web.  The web application substitutes for the trained facilitator.  Users are guided through a six-step process that takes them from establishing a shared vision, identifying metrics and common goals, and planning and tracking actions. Each step is equivalent to the level of an online game.  User/players are awarded points for ideas and collaborative behavior; they are dinged for negative behaviors.  Users are given scores for the expertise they apply to a single problem, and each receives a lifetime problem solver score.  Scores can translate to real-world benefits through enhanced reputations that lead to real-world, compensated assignments.

Description: EZ-Ticket.com, LLC (EZ-Ticket) is an internet ticket broker that resells event tickets to concerts, sporting events, theatre shows.
Full Description: EZ-Ticket.com, LLC (EZ-Ticket) is an internet ticket broker that resells event tickets to concerts, sporting events, theatre shows and other events requiring ticketing.  The secondary ticket market, according to Forrester Research, is a $4.5 billion a year industry in the US.  Currently sales through mobile applications are virtually untapped, however, they are forecast to amount to 50% of the market in the next few years.  EZ-Ticket currently has over 130 marketing and mobile application websites to allow the streamlined purchase of event tickets by concert and sports fans.  EZ-Ticket is in the process of launching an IP television platform with our subsidiary Bigado.TV in the Fall of 2012 based on sports and entertainment to compliment our ticket sales.  The majority of EZ-Ticket's events are in the Dallas Metropolitan market with coverage expanding nationwide.  Traditionally, the secondary ticket market has been associated with illegal scalping in front of a venue. EZ-Ticket is legitimizing this process by acquiring premium seats through its network and selling them through its storefront and internet site, while also providing safety and convenience to its clients.

Full Description: We built a unique way for online daters to spark genuine connections without the superficial bias of popular dating apps. Dwindle Dating allows users to instantly play a 21st century version of the popular TV game show…”The Dating Game”. The game begins by entering a chat with your “date”, whose photo is camouflaged among a group of 4 other Dwindle user photos. It’s up to you and your match to engage in a real conversation to solve the mystery. The more you chat, the quicker the decoy photos start to disappear. As the decoys “dwindle down” you unlock additional photos for each one remaining.  By the time you’ve successfully revealed your match, you’ve had a chance to connect in a way not possible with other dating apps. Keep chatting with all your successful matches anytime through the app.  The Los Angeles beta launch for iOS begins in November 2015 with expansion to other major U.S cities in 2016.
